#Imputing missing values by mean
Data['Life_Expectancy_Both'] = Data['Life_Expectancy_Both'].fillna(Data.groupby('Country')['Life_Expectancy_Both'].transform('mean'))
Data['Life_Expectancy_Males'] = Data['Life_Expectancy_Males'].fillna(Data.groupby('Country')['Life_Expectancy_Males'].transform('mean'))
Data['Life_Expectancy_Females'] = Data['Life_Expectancy_Females'].fillna(Data.groupby('Country')['Life_Expectancy_Females'].transform('mean'))
Data['Under5_Mortality_Both'] = Data['Under5_Mortality_Both'].fillna(Data.groupby('Country')['Under5_Mortality_Both'].transform('mean'))
Data['Under5_Mortality_Males'] = Data['Under5_Mortality_Males'].fillna(Data.groupby('Country')['Under5_Mortality_Males'].transform('mean'))
Data['Under5_Mortality_Females'] = Data['Under5_Mortality_Females'].fillna(Data.groupby('Country')['Under5_Mortality_Females'].transform('mean'))

To answer this question, first analyse the variability of the values within the individual subregions and then compare the measures of central tendency of the individual variables between different subregions.¶

In [56]:
# Set up the subplots using gridspec
fig = plt.figure(figsize=(18, 6))
gs = gridspec.GridSpec(1, 3)

# Boxplot for Life Expectancy (Both Sexes)
ax0 = plt.subplot(gs[0])
box0 = ax0.boxplot([dataframe_2004['Life_Expectancy_Both'], dataframe_2024['Life_Expectancy_Both']], labels=['2004', '2024'])
ax0.set_xlabel('Years')
ax0.set_ylabel('L.E.')
ax0.set_title('L.E. (Both Sexes)', fontsize=20)

# Count outliers for Life Expectancy (Both Sexes)
outliers0 = [flier.get_ydata() for flier in box0['fliers']]
outliers_count0 = sum(len(outliers) for outliers in outliers0)
ax0.text(0.95, 0.05, f'Outliers: {outliers_count0}', transform=ax0.transAxes, fontsize=20, ha='right', va='bottom')

# Boxplot for Life Expectancy (Males)
ax1 = plt.subplot(gs[1])
box1 = ax1.boxplot([dataframe_2004['Life_Expectancy_Males'], dataframe_2024['Life_Expectancy_Males']], labels=['2004', '2024'])
ax1.set_xlabel('Years')
ax1.set_ylabel('L.E.')
ax1.set_title('L.E. (Males)', fontsize=20)

# Count outliers for Life Expectancy (Males)
outliers1 = [flier.get_ydata() for flier in box1['fliers']]
outliers_count1 = sum(len(outliers) for outliers in outliers1)
ax1.text(0.95, 0.05, f'Outliers: {outliers_count1}', transform=ax1.transAxes, fontsize=20, ha='right', va='bottom')

# Boxplot for Life Expectancy (Females)
ax2 = plt.subplot(gs[2])
box2 = ax2.boxplot([dataframe_2004['Life_Expectancy_Females'], dataframe_2024['Life_Expectancy_Females']], labels=['2004', '2024'])

# Create a label encoder
label_encoder = LabelEncoder()

# Encode the regions as numerical values
dataframe_2004['Region_Encoded'] = label_encoder.fit_transform(dataframe_2004['Region'])

# Set up the subplots using gridspec
fig = plt.figure(figsize=(18, 6))
gs = gridspec.GridSpec(1, 4, width_ratios=[1, 1, 1, 0.1])

# Scatter plot for Life Expectancy (Both Sexes)
ax0 = plt.subplot(gs[0])
scatter0 = ax0.scatter(dataframe_2004['Life_Expectancy_Both'], dataframe_2024['Life_Expectancy_Both'], c=dataframe_2004['Region_Encoded'], cmap='viridis')
ax0.set_xlabel('2004', fontsize=20)
ax0.set_ylabel('2024', fontsize=20)
ax0.set_title('Life Expectancy (Both Sexes)', fontsize=14)

# Scatter plot for Life Expectancy (Males)
ax1 = plt.subplot(gs[1])
scatter1 = ax1.scatter(dataframe_2004['Life_Expectancy_Males'], dataframe_2024['Life_Expectancy_Males'], c=dataframe_2004['Region_Encoded'], cmap='viridis')
ax1.set_xlabel('2004', fontsize=20)
ax1.set_ylabel('2024', fontsize=20)
ax1.set_title('Life Expectancy (Males)', fontsize=14)

# Scatter plot for Life Expectancy (Females)
ax2 = plt.subplot(gs[2])

ax2.set_xlabel('2004', fontsize=20)
ax2.set_ylabel('2024', fontsize=20)
ax2.set_title('Life Expectancy (Females)', fontsize=14)
